===Etymology===
{{ja-adj-ku|赤し|aka}} Cognate with {{m|ja|明るい|tr=akarui||bright}}.

Hamano (2000)<ref>Hamano, S. Journal of East Asian Linguistics (2000) 9: 207. https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1008367619295</ref> proposes that medial voiceless plosives, like {{IPAchar|/-k-/}}, underwent voicing, then affrication, and gliding, before being dropped; before {{IPAchar|/-i, -u, -e, -o/}}. As this sound-change did not occur before {{IPAchar|/-a/}}, Middle Japanese {{IPAchar|/akaki/}} would have become {{IPAchar|/akai/}} [[赤い]].

{{IPAfont|⟨akaki<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → *{{IPAfont|/akakʲi/}} → *{{IPAfont|/akagʲi/}} → *{{IPAfont|/akaɣi/}} → *{{IPAfont|/akaji/}} → *{{IPAfont|/akai/}}.

